# CI/CD Pipeline

## Workflow Structure
```
validate.yml (on: push/PR to main)
  ├── _audit_and_lint.yml
  │     ├── bundler-audit --update
  │     ├── brakeman -q -w2
  │     ├── importmap audit
  │     └── rubocop --parallel -f github
  └── _tests.yml
        ├── db:schema:load (not db:migrate)
        ├── db:migrate + git diff --exit-code (schema drift check)
        └── bin/rake (full RSpec suite)

deploy.yml (on: workflow_dispatch)
  ├── Inputs: environment (production/staging), instance (easydoctor/monzino)
  ├── Optional: run lint_and_tests first
  └── .github/actions/deploy → Kamal → ghcr.io
```

## Rules for GitHub Actions Changes
- Never skip CI steps without team approval
- Schema drift check must stay: `db:migrate && git diff --exit-code`
- Secrets via GitHub repository/environment secrets — never hardcoded
- `concurrency` group prevents duplicate workflow runs (cancel-in-progress: true)

## Merge Rules
- Squash merge to `main` only
- All jobs in `validate.yml` must be green before merge
- Branch protection enforced on `main`

## Deploy
- Manual trigger only via `workflow_dispatch`
- Always run with `lint_and_tests: true` for production
- Instance-specific secrets: `EASYDOCTOR_SECRETS`, `MONZINO_SECRETS`
- Kamal config: `config/deploy.yml`, Docker image built for `amd64`
